        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 29 at 9:31PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 930 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Calhan, or 30 miles east of Colorado Springs, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Ramah and Calhan.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
